Masters in Public Health (MPH) in the UK: Eligibility, Courses, Admission, Top Universities, Scholarships

  • 197 Reads
  • 3 min Read
  • By:CANAM Group
  • Updated On:Jun 21,2023 05:37 PM IST

Public Health is an expanding field, attracting people all over the world. Read the blog to know everything in detail about studying Masters in Public Health from top universities of the United Kingdom to advance your career in public health.

Public health is a multidisciplinary field that aims to advance and safeguard global health. Students who pursue a Masters in Public Health (MPH) degree are better prepared to solve complicated public health issues. World-class education, top ranked universities and excellent research facilities makes UK an ideal destination for students to pursue Masters in Public Health.

Read further to get a detailed overview of Masters in Public Health degree in UK, including admission requirements, best universities, course structure, career prospects and more.

Why study Masters in Public Health in UK?

As an aspiring public health professional, you may be wondering why to choose UK for studying Masters in Public Health. Let’s look at its reasons.

  • Three universities of UK namely, The University of Oxford, University of Cambridge and University College London (UCL) are ranked in top 10 universities of the world.
  • The program duration of Masters in Public Health degree in UK is shorter as compared to other countries which helps to reduce student’s overall cost of education.
  • Public Health is one of the highest paid professions in the world.

Course Highlights

Degree LevelMasters
Course Duration1 to 2 years
Eligibility CriteriaBachelor’s degree with minimum 60%
SpecializationsHealth Education, Health Economics, Epidemiology,  Occupational Health Safety
English Proficiency TestIELTS, TOEFL

Course Structure for Masters in Public Health in UK

Masters in Public Health programs are designed to be completed in 1 year of full-time study or 2 years of part-time study. The course curriculum of a MPH program in UK includes the following core subjects.

  • Epidemiology
  • Biostatistics
  • Health policy
  • Health promotion
  • Environmental Health

In addition to the coursework, most MPH programs in UK also require students to complete a research project which provides students an opportunity to apply their gained knowledge and skills to the real-world.

Eligibility for Masters in Public Health in UK Admission

Given below is the eligibility criteria to study Masters in Public Health in UK -

  • A bachelor’s degree in science related field with minimum 60%
  • English proficiency test scores of IELTS or TOEFL exam
  • A relevant work experience (if applicable)
  • Proof of basic math and computer skills

Documents Required for Masters in Public Health in UK

  • Academic Transcripts
  • Proof of English language proficiency (IELTS or TOEFL)
  • Statement of Purpose (SOP)
  • CV/ Resume
  •  Letters of Recommendation
  •  Course-specific required documents

Job Prospects after Public Health Course in UK

Numerous public health job opportunities are available for Public Health graduates in UK and Public Health workers in UK are third-highest paid in the world. Some of the high paying job titles after completing Masters in Public Health are-

  • Social and Health Program Consultant
  • Public Health Analyst
  • Health Promotion Specialist
  • Epidemiologist
  • Health Policy Advisor
  • Environmental Health Officer
  • Global Health Consultant
  • Deputy Director

Pursuing Masters in Public Health from renowned universities of UK offers rewarding opportunities to students. Also, public health is a growing field and one of the highest paying professions. FAQ

How much does it cost to study Masters in Public Health in UK?
Studying Masters in Public Health in UK costs 19,800 GBP to 38,000 GBP. The tuition fee varies depending upon the program and university.
Which are the best universities to study MPH in UK?
University of Cambridge, University College London (UCL), University of Edinburgh, University of Manchester, and King's College London are the most popular and top ranked universities to study MPH in UK.
What is the course duration of Masters in Public Health program in UK?
Masters in Public Health is a 1-2 years long program which can be taken full-time or part-time.
Which are the highest-paying job roles after completing a Masters in Public Health in UK?
Scientist – £31,805 per year
Social and Health Program Consultant – £92,214 per year
Locum Consultant – £89,627 per year
Scientist – £31,805 per year
Senior Scientist – £43,875 per year
Environmental Scientist – £37,580 per year
Is public health a good career option to pursue in UK?
Public Health is a high demand career in UK which pays very well. Students have several job opportunities available after Masters in Public Health in UK such as Social and Health Program Consultant, Public Health Analyst, Health Promotion Specialist, Epidemiologist and Health Policy Advisor.
